A ranar 11 ga Maris, 2020, Hukumar Lafiya ta Duniya ta bayyana COVID-19 a matsayin annoba.
Don magance kamuwa da cutar SARS-CoV-2, ƙungiyarmu ta kirkiro gajeren jagorar bincike kuma ta buga shi a yanar gizo a shafin yanar gizon mujallar Military Medical Research a ranar 6 ga Fabrairu, 2020.
Wannan littafin ya jawo hankalin mutane sosai.
A wannan lokacin, COVID-19 sabon cuta ne, don haka fahimtarmu da iliminmu sun ƙaru a hankali bisa ga binciken da aka samu a yanzu da kuma kwarewar asibiti; don haka dabarun bincike da ayyukan magani suna ci gaba da sabuntawa.
Alal misali, a tsakanin 16 ga Janairu zuwa 3 ga Maris, 2020, an fitar da takardun 7 na Shawarwarin Gwaji da Magani ga COVID-19, wanda Kwamitin Lafiya na Kasa na kasar Sin (http://www.nhc.gov.cn/) ya wallafa, kuma an sauya wasu ka'idojinsa.
Zhou da kuma wasu daga cikin marubuta sun yi wani bincike da ya ba da bayani game da shawarwarinmu, kuma sun ba da shawarwari masu sauƙi game da ganewar asali bisa ga ilimin asibiti.
Wannan aikin ya kara da cewa mun samu wasu sababbin shaidu masu amfani, kuma ya ba da bayanai masu amfani game da wannan annoba da ta shafi duniya.
Muna nuna godiya ga aikin da suka yi kuma muna nuna cewa suna da muhimmanci sosai.
Duk da haka, bisa ga sabon fitowar Shawarwarin bincike da magani don COVID-19 (suna gwaji na bakwai) da kuma sakamakon binciken da ake yi a yanzu, kuma aikin su yana bukatar sabuntawa.
A cewar fitowar bakwai ta wannan takaddar (daga 3 ga Maris, 2020), don gudanar da bincike mai zurfi yayin tabbatar da zargin cutar ya zama dole a haɗa wani abu ɗaya daga cikin bayanan tarihin cututtukan cututtuka tare da bayyanar cututtuka biyu:
Tarihin cututtukan cututtuka: (1) tarihin motsi ko kasancewa a Wuhan da kewaye da shi ko kuma a wasu mazaunan da aka samu COVID-19 a cikin kwanaki 14 kafin bayyanar cututtuka; (2) tarihin hulɗa da marasa lafiya da ke da cutar SARS-CoV-2 (tare da gwajin gwajin nucleic acid); (3) tarihin hulɗa da marasa lafiya da ke da zafin jiki ko alamun numfashi daga Wuhan da kewaye da shi ko kuma daga wasu mazaunan da aka samu COVID-19 a cikin kwanaki 14 kafin bayyanar cututtuka; (4) tarihin hulɗa da ƙungiyoyin marasa lafiya da suka tabbatar da cutar (≥ 2 lokuta da ke da alamun zafin jiki ko alamun numfashi, kamar su dakunan makaranta da dakunan aji, dakunan aji, da wuraren aji na tsawon makonni 2 da aka yi rajista).
Abubuwan da ke faruwa a asibiti: (1) zafin jiki da kuma/ko alamun numfashi; (2) bayyanar bayyanar COVID-19 na waje; (3) yawan kwayoyin cutar leukocyte na al'ada ko kuma ya ragu tare da raguwar yawan kwayoyin lymphocytes a farkon bayyanar cututtuka.
Ana iya gano wani mutum da aka tabbatar da cutar ne bisa ga wata sanadiyar cutar da ke nuna cewa akwai wata hujja ta hanyar kamuwa da cuta ko kuma wani abu mai kama da cutar, wato: (1) gwajin PCR na ainihi yana da kyau ga SARS-CoV-2; (2) cikakken tsarin tsara kwayar cutar yana nuna babban daidaituwa game da sabon coronavirus; (3) sakamako mai kyau na serotest ga magungunan IgM da IgG na musamman ga SARS-CoV-2; ko canza sakamakon gwajin daga mummunan zuwa tabbatacce ga magungunan IgG na musamman ga SARS-CoV-2, ko ƙaruwa a cikin titra aƙalla sau 4 a lokacin warkewa game da alamar da ta dace a cikin mawuyacin lokaci.
Hakanan za'a iya lura cewa a cikin na biyu (18 ga Janairu, 2020) da na uku (22 ga Janairu, 2020) na wannan takaddar an ƙara gwajin PCR na ainihin lokaci don nucleic acid a cikin numfashi ko kuma gwajin jini.
An ƙara binciken cututtukan jini a fitowar na huɗu (27 ga Janairu, 2020) da na biyar (8 ga Fabrairu, 2020); sannan a fitowar ta bakwai an ƙara buƙatar tabbacin serological.
Waɗannan canje-canjen sun dogara ne akan ci gaba da bincike na masu bincike da ke neman mafi kyawun tsari don gano nucleic acid a cikin sauri, da kuma nazarin samfurin numfashi, gami da zaɓi na jini, wanda ke ƙara samun samfurori daban-daban kuma yana taimakawa wajen haɗa sakamakon gwajin tabbatacce don takamaiman antibodies cikin ƙimar tabbatar da cutar.
Duk da haka, akwai ƙarin tabbaci game da yin hankali a lokacin da ake kula da marasa lafiya da ba su da alamun bayyanar cututtuka.
