Hukumomin kiwon lafiya na Koriya da na kasar Sin sun ba da shawarar yin amfani da chlorine.
Cibiyar Kwayar cutar Wuhan ta ba da shawarar yin amfani da gram guda a kowace rana, amma ta ce sau biyu yana da haɗari sosai kuma yana iya haifar da mutuwa.
A ranar 28 ga Maris, 2020, FDA ta ba da izinin gaggawa don amfani da hydroxychloroquine da chlorine a kan shawarar likitoci da ke kula da marasa lafiya da COVID-19.
Bayanai na farko sun nuna cewa ana bukatar karin rigakafin ribavirin don hana SARS-CoV-2 a cikin in vitro.
An ba da shawarar yin nazarin nitasoxanide a cikin in vivo, yana nuna hana SARS-CoV-2 a ƙananan taro. Bincike ya nuna cewa don shiga SARS-CoV-2 ta hanyar hulɗa da mai karɓar ACE2 yana buƙatar daidaita ƙwayoyin cuta na transmembrane protease serine 2 (TMPRSS2).
Binciken amfani da chlorine da hydroxychloroquine tare da azithromycin ko ba tare da shi ba yana da ƙuntatawa mai tsanani wanda ke hana ƙungiyar likitanci yin amfani da waɗannan hanyoyin magani ba tare da ƙarin bincike ba. Ozeltavir ba ya hana SARS-CoV-2 in vitro, kuma rawar da yake takawa a cikin maganin COVID-19.
Za a iya samun hypercytoquinemia a matsayin rikitarwa a ƙarshen COVID-19.
